This construction gives rise to a smooth compact three dimensional toric
variety  (smooth because the generators of every cone are also
generators of , compact because the fan fills ).
The loci  are the toric divisors .

To any lattice point  of  we can assign a monomial
; the exponents are nonnegative as a
consequence of reflexivity.
The hypersurface defined by a generic polynomial 
transforms homogeneously under () and can be shown to define
a K3 hypersurface in .

